               <p>I <rs id="t17901027-59-viclabel320" type="occupation">deal in hardware and second hand clothes</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17901027-59-victim697 t17901027-59-viclabel320"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t17901027-59-crimeloc321">High-street, St. Giles's</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17901027-59-crimeloc321" type="placeName" value="High-street, St. Giles's"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17901027-59-crimeloc321" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17901027-59-off318 t17901027-59-crimeloc321"></join>. I lost a coat; I saw it an hour before; it hung up for sale: it was on Monday, the 27th of September: I took him the 28th.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17901027-59-person699">
                  MICHAEL
                   RYAN
               <interp inst="t17901027-59-person699" type="surname" value="RYAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17901027-59-person699" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17901027-59-person699" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I work with the prosecutor. I saw the prisoner take the coat: I was in the back shop: I saw him lap the coat under his arm: I thought then he had bought it: it was about one o'clock: I saw his face: he asked me the price of a coat before he took this: he came the night following to the shop; I came down off the counter immediately; I went out and took him: he said nothing. I do not know a halfpennyworth more.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17901027-59-person700">
                  SUSANNAH
                   BURNETT
               <interp inst="t17901027-59-person700" type="surname" value="BURNETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17901027-59-person700" type="given" value="SUSANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17901027-59-person700" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I keep a shoe shop next door: he came past my shop nine or ten times: I sent a girl to watch him; that was about a minute before he took the coat: it was about one o'clock on Monday.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17901027-59-person701">
                  ANN
                   SLATER
               <interp inst="t17901027-59-person701" type="surname" value="SLATER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17901027-59-person701" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17901027-59-person701" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>Mrs. Burnett told me to watch a man: I did not see his face; but I saw him take the coat: his back was towards me: he came the next afternoon, about four o'clock.</p>
               <p>Mrs. Burnett. I am sure to the man.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. I never had my coat again.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I know nothing of it: that day he says I took the coat I was at work.</p>
